  {
    "type": "main-inset-br",
    "page": "60",
    "head": { "title": { "en": "PCB BOARD", "zh": "PCB 板" }, "small": "board_40" },
    "main": { "src": "board_40_teflon_assembled_cam0_nrvk.svg", "style": "transform: translateX(-35mm);" },
    "notes": [
      {
        "h3": { "en": "Teflon tube", "zh": "特氟龙管" },
        "body": { "en": "Run the wires through the Teflon tube — it keeps them tidy and clear of the moving belts and motors.", "zh": "把导线穿进特氟龙管——既能理顺线缆，又能让它们避开运动中的同步带和电机。" },
        "classes": "note overlay sm",
        "style": "right:30mm; top:30mm; width:90mm;"
      },
      {
        "h3": { "en": "Rough length", "zh": "大致长度" },
        "body": { "en": "Make the tube about 380 mm — long enough to reach from the PCB board to the X carriage at its farthest position.", "zh": "管子取约 380 mm 长——足够从 PCB 板一直够到 X 滑座的最远位置。" },
        "classes": "note overlay sm",
        "style": "right:30mm; top:50mm; width:90mm;"
      },
      {
        "h3": { "en": "Extend the solenoid leads", "zh": "加长电磁阀引线" },
        "body": { "en": "The solenoid's stock leads are too short to reach the board — splice on extra wire to connect the solenoid to the PCB.", "zh": "电磁阀的原装引线太短，够不到板子——接上一段导线，把电磁阀连到 PCB。" },
        "classes": "note overlay sm",
        "style": "right:30mm; top:80mm; width:90mm;"
      },
      {
        "h3": { "en": "PTFE vs FEP", "zh": "PTFE 与 FEP" },
        "body": { "en": "Either tube works here — PTFE (milky white) or FEP (clear). The toughness/stiffness is enough to support the wire.", "zh": "两种管子都行——PTFE（乳白色）或 FEP（透明）。其韧性和刚性足以撑住导线。" },
        "classes": "note overlay sm",
        "style": "right:30mm; top:110mm; width:90mm;"
      }
    ],
    "bom": {
      "label": { "en": "Bill of materials", "zh": "物料清单" },
